00:00:02.159 --> 00:00:07.299
&gt;&gt;Dr. Atul Sharma: For all conditions, if
you look at men and women, if they have diabetes,

00:00:07.299 --> 00:00:13.181
they are three times more likely to die from
heart disease, no matter what they do. The

00:00:13.181 --> 00:00:18.020
only piece of good news is this study done
in The New England Journal in 2002 that looked

00:00:18.020 --> 00:00:24.570
at people who were at risk of developing diabetes,
and they randomized these people to three

00:00:24.570 --> 00:00:29.619
different groups. They gave one group of people
a sugar pill, one group they gave a diabetes

00:00:29.619 --> 00:00:35.350
medicine that has been shown to prevent diabetes,
and in the third group they said 'here's your

00:00:35.350 --> 00:00:40.420
diet, we want you to exercise 30 minutes four
times a week'. And they followed them for

00:00:40.420 --> 00:00:44.190
four years and you can see that the rate of
developing diabetes if you did nothing is

00:00:44.190 --> 00:00:50.090
58 percent in this group. If you took the
medication, the rate of developing diabetes

00:00:50.090 --> 00:00:56.710
is 31 percent. And if you adhered just to
lifestyle changes and didn't take medication,

00:00:56.710 --> 00:01:01.650
the rate of developing diabetes was 19 percent.
So diabetes can be prevented, which is probably

00:01:01.650 --> 00:01:06.160
the single most important thing that we need
to know from this slide.

00:01:06.160 --> 00:01:13.690
I'm going to talk a little about stress and
heart disease and stress and women and heart

00:01:13.690 --> 00:01:20.750
