published in the Journal of Circulation. And

00:01:25.810 --> 00:01:29.490
this is what it looks like, it's called, you
may have heard of it, it's called "Broken

00:01:29.490 --> 00:01:34.890
Heart" syndrome or sad heart syndrome or the
real name is stress-induced cardiomyopathy

00:01:34.890 --> 00:01:39.929
or Takotsubo's Cardiomyopathy. But this is
a picture of the main pumping chamber of the

00:01:39.929 --> 00:01:45.030
heart, and there's a catheter in here that
you really can't see very clearly. The catheter

00:01:45.030 --> 00:01:50.390
is injecting dye into the main pumping chamber.
