Most of the data on psychological stress and
psycho-social stress comes from a number of

00:05:06.680 --> 00:05:12.200
European studies and this is the biggest one.
Eleven thousand patients and thirteen thousand

00:05:12.200 --> 00:05:17.100
controls. They took people that were matched
for age, for sex, for gender, for occupation

00:05:17.100 --> 00:05:24.621
and matched them as best they could and they
asked them to classify their stressors. Whether

00:05:24.621 --> 00:05:30.500
they were work stress, home stress, financial
stress or major life issues. And they just

00:05:30.500 --> 00:05:35.490
followed these people for years. And they
found that people who classified themselves

00:05:35.490 --> 00:05:41.280
as having one or more stressors were four
times more likely to have heart disease and

00:05:41.280 --> 00:05:48.470
have heart events, whether it's a stress-induced
cardiomyopathy, sudden death, other conditions,

00:05:48.470 --> 00:05:55.030
other cardiomyopathies that are unexplained
or heart attacks. Another case, cardiovascular

00:05:55.030 --> 00:05:59.700
events during the World Cup. This is actually
true of the Super Bowl, too. Viewing a stressful

00:05:59.700 --> 00:06:04.850
soccer match more than doubles the risk of
acute cardiovascular event. In fact, in this

00:06:04.850 --> 00:06:10.260
article the authors actually said that they
need to have preventive measures, I don't

00:06:10.260 --> 00:06:13.330
know what those preventive measures would
be, but they need to take preventive measures

00:06:13.330 --> 00:06:16.580
when the World Cup is on. [laughter] I don't
even know what they would do, but something

00:06:16.580 --> 00:06:23.290
like that, right? Overtime work. Overtime
work associated with an increased risk of

00:06:23.290 --> 00:06:30.400
developing heart disease. Being on call 24
hours, as a doctor, associated with an increased

00:06:30.400 --> 00:06:36.090
risk of heart disease. In fact, this is one
of the reasons that the laws have changed

00:06:36.090 --> 00:06:41.600
for physician work hours in Australia and
in the U.K. way before they changed here,

00:06:41.600 --> 00:06:47.500
but they finally changed here, too. That people
were developing stress-induced cardiomyopathies

00:06:47.500 --> 00:06:54.040
and heart disease working 24-hour shifts.
Now, we don't really know why this happens,

00:06:54.040 --> 00:07:00.419
but stress leads to direct biological effects,
physical strain, hormonal changes, it leads

00:07:00.419 --> 00:07:06.190
to maladaptive coping behaviors, such as smoking
or eating excessively, drinking excessive,

00:07:06.190 --> 00:07:11.100
alcohol. And then there are emotional immediate
effects on diet and activity levels and they

00:07:11.100 --> 00:07:18.070
all lead to increased risk of disease. The
body's response to stress is usually one of

00:07:18.070 --> 00:07:23.420
three, a set of three different phases. The
first phase is an acute alarm phase, where

00:07:23.420 --> 00:07:27.740
you kind of everyone knows what it feels like
when you feel stressed, you get dry mouth,

00:07:27.740 --> 00:07:33.919
your hands get sweaty, you feel your heart
racing. Over time as you get used to the same

00:07:33.919 --> 00:07:38.330
stressor, your body develops a kind of a tolerance
and a, and an acceptance of that level of

00:07:38.330 --> 00:07:42.990
stress. And that's where most people are.
They're in high states of psycho-social stress

00:07:42.990 --> 00:07:48.550
and they've kind of learned to resist those
effects on their body because they couldn't

00:07:48.550 --> 00:07:52.770
have that same kind of effect for an extended
period of time. Eventually over time, the

00:07:52.770 --> 00:08:01.180
theory is that the energy sources become depleted
and the ability to resist stressors goes down.

00:08:01.180 --> 00:08:07.139
