00:41:16.069 --> 00:41:22.640
shown to reduce sugar levels and increase
energy levels. This is the study that looks

00:41:22.640 --> 00:41:31.249
at behavior therapy and risk for heart disease
and I'll just circle the conclusion. A cognitive

00:41:31.249 --> 00:41:35.049
behavioral therapy approach reduces the risk
of recurrent heart disease in people who have

00:41:35.049 --> 00:41:39.319
previous heart attacks. And what did they
incorporate? They incorporated group therapy

00:41:39.319 --> 00:41:43.460
to discuss common stressors. So if you have
something that stresses you out, find a group

00:41:43.460 --> 00:41:48.619
of people, your friends most likely, who have
those same stresses, very easy to talk about

00:41:48.619 --> 00:41:53.130
it. If you build social networks to handle
your chronic stress, you're much more likely

00:41:53.130 --> 00:41:59.130
to be able to deal with that stress. Improving
your interpersonal relationships by being

00:41:59.130 --> 00:42:05.359
direct and honest instead of kind of holding
on to that irritation and anger, just tell

00:42:05.359 --> 00:42:08.690
